definition: to melt (metal)/to cancel or annul/to sell/to spend/to fasten with a bolt/bolt or pin

sentences.english: After the "three in one", the enterprise wants to cancel the operation?

sentences.english: Ross, listen, if you do not get this annulment, I will.

sentences.english: None were cancelled or lapsed during the period.

sentences.english: Many times a substantial portion of your leasing costs can be written off.

sentences.english: Unfortunately since you have already canceled the hosting we cannot re-instate this account.

sentences.english: Severe violators will have their teaching licenses revoked.

sentences.english: When I cancelled my membership, I felt liberated.

sentences.english: The corporation can hold this stock indefinitely or can reissue or retire it.

sentences.english: Use this to dynamically unregister modifier plugin. Pass in the template modifier name.

The designated officer is to sign-off on the register.

sentences.english: The termination of association shall be subject to the cancellation formalities by the judicial administrative organ of the province level.
sentences.chinese: 終止聯營的，由省級司法行政機關辦理註銷手續。

sentences.english: You can even write off business debts.
sentences.chinese: 你甚至可以註銷交易債務。
